      • getFeed

        public void getFeed(WebAPI.GetFeedCallback callback,
           java.util.List<SubscriptionItem> subscriptions,
           int first,
           int count)
        Method using the web-API call "getFeed.php". The returned set of data is a reverse-chronological list of reviews, and is based on ONE or MULTIPLE courses.
        Parameters:
        callback - The object to receive the finish-notifications.
        subscriptions - The list of subscription items to be included in the result set.
        first - The first item to be returned.
        count - The maximum number of items to be returned.

      • getFeed

        public void getFeed(WebAPI.GetFeedCallback callback,
           java.util.List<SubscriptionItem> subscriptions,
           int first,
           int count,
           int lastId)
        Method using the web-API call "getFeed.php". The returned set of data is a reverse-chronological list of reviews, and is based on ONE or MULTIPLE courses. The "first" parameter is ignored, and all returned items will have a lower ID than "lastId".
        Parameters:
        callback - The object to receive the finish-notifications.
        subscriptions - The list of subscription items to be included in the result set.
        first - Value is irrelevant as it is ignored by the web API.
        count - The maximum number of items to be returned.
        lastId - The ID of the last review the web API should ignore.

      • getFeed

        public void getFeed(WebAPI.GetFeedCallback callback,
           java.lang.String lectureHash,
           int first,
           int count)
        Method using the web-API call "getFeed.php". The returned set of data is a reverse-chronological list of reviews, and is based on a SINGLE lecture.
        Parameters:
        callback - The object to receive the finish-notifications.
        lectureHash - The hash of the lecture from which to retrieve a feed.
        first - The first item to be returned.
        count - The maximum number of items to be returned.

        Parameters:

        Method using the web-API call "postReview.php".
        Parameters:
        context - The context is used to retrieve the ANDROID_ID value when passing the clienthash parameter.
        callback - The callback to receive the finish-notifications.
        review - LectureReviewItem containing the information to be posted to the web-API.
